								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2676">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I enjoyed reading your January 1997 issue, especially &ldquo;<a href="/article/1824">This Thing about Goodness</a>,&rdquo; by Alison Luterman. Her voice was so direct, so clear and courageous. I was deeply moved by her situation and those of the women she described. I also cut out John Spivey&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/1817">Coyote Genesis</a>&rdquo; for my &ldquo;keep&rdquo; file. I had been considering ending my subscription &mdash; it&rsquo;s hard to find time to read all the great books <em>and</em> magazines &mdash; but after that issue, I decided I just couldn&rsquo;t let it lapse.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author"><a href="/contributors/priscilla-frake">Priscilla Frake</a><br>San Ramon, California</p>
